A days-old baby was found abandoned outside the Nairobi Womens Hospital Kirichwa Road branch on Friday morning.A male nurse found the baby at the front gate, wrapped in a blue vest, black sweatshirt and a jacket.The boy was taken to the nursery, cleaned, dressed, fed and taken for tests.&ldquo;From the tests, the baby is healthy,&rdquo; communications officer Geoffrey Korio said in a statement on Friday.&ldquo;Through the Gender Violence Recovery Centre, the baby has secured safe placement at a reputable children&rsquo;s home."The hospital, which has now rescued two babies in three weeks, reported the matter at Kilimani police station.